      "rationale": "The primary QoI (peak interface micromotion and cumulative subsidence) directly correspond to the clinical acceptance criterion (subsidence < 150 µm for osseointegration). The mapping from model output to clinical threshold is documented in the device specification and confirmed by the clinical team. Secondary QoIs (contact pressure distribution, von Mises stress in tibial tray) are reported as supporting evidence.",
