      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum model with Coulomb friction contact is justified for the pre-osseointegration subsidence regime (< 500 cycles, small strain). Bone is modeled as heterogeneous isotropic elastic with density-modulus relationships from Kopperdahl and Keaveny (1998), validated against nanoindentation data in the study dataset. Viscoelastic creep and bone remodeling are explicitly scoped out with documented justification that their contribution to peak subsidence within 500 cycles is less than 5% based on published literature.",
